title: Great stellated truncated dodecahedron
summary: In geometry, the great stellated truncated dodecahedron (or quasitruncated great stellated dodecahedron or great stellatruncated dodecahedron) is a nonconvex uniform polyhedron, indexed as U66. It has 32 faces (20 triangles and 12 decagrams), 90 edges, and 60 vertices.[1] It is given a Schl√§fli symbol t0,1{5/3,3}.
